modules.description: This module provides asynchronous functions for accessing and manipulating memory-mapped files, including reading integers of various sizes and endiannesses, strings, and raw memory slices. It works with typed memory representations (`Cachet.t`) and supports cooperative multitasking through Lwt, yielding control during I/O operations. Concrete use cases include parsing binary file formats, implementing custom serialization, and efficiently accessing large memory-mapped datasets without blocking other concurrent tasks.
